&ldquo;DOD charged the American taxpayer $43 million for what is likely the world&rsquo;s most expensive gas station.&rdquo;
That&rsquo;s what Special Inspector General John F. Sopko found when he looked at the construction of a natural gas station in Sheberghan, Afghanistan.
According to the report, at most that station should have cost about $500,000. But in this case, the Department of Defense&rsquo;s Task Force for Stability and Business Operations awarded Central Asian Engineering a contract to build the station for a little under $3 million.

